This paper is about improving acoustic modeling for speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and batch normalization (BN), which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of context in modeling, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
